Honestly, this comments section just gets depressing at times. He’s a movie critic reviewing a film, but some people seem to believe that he is somehow starting a Marxist revolution because he said a film was okay.

If people actually heard themselves. This is it guys. The fall of the capitalist regime and the start of the glorious communist revolution because in his three minute and twenty eight second review of a film, Mark Kermode called Birds of Prey “okay and entertaining”.

It’s not woke. It’s not to do with it being a female ensemble. It’s not any of that. Take down the chalkboard and put away the strings. The secret is this: it’s not some great “leftist revolution” that Kermode thought the film was okay and entertaining, it’s because the film was probably okay and probably entertaining.

snippet.textDisplay:
I went into this review expecting the best Mr. Kermode could say about it would be some damned-by-faint-praise phrasing like "It's at least better than Suicide Squad was." He seems to have actually liked it somewhat though, which is rather surprising.

I still couldn't care less about it myself though, which is why I watched the review in the first place since I didn't care about potential spoilers. Even with the seemingly positive review, it just sounds too busy character-wise for me to care about when most of these characters are just being introduced (which proves WB still hasn't realized that can be a problem), especially since I still don't care for this rebooted version of Harley Quinn at all.

Oh well. Maybe the Wonder Woman sequel will be worth seeing, not that I'll hold my breath.
